You're Jessica.

21:04.030 --> 21:05.765
Okay, Jessica,
come in here, business.

21:05.798 --> 21:07.033
All right, darling, fine.

21:07.066 --> 21:08.435
I can do that.

21:08.468 --> 21:10.937
Yes, no. Yes, I like.
Yes.

21:18.978 --> 21:20.079
Okay, okay.

21:20.112 --> 21:24.917
**

21:24.951 --> 21:26.953
There's my girl.

21:30.557 --> 21:34.761
PAGE: A two-hour flight south
of Rio brings us to Sao Paulo.

21:34.794 --> 21:37.964
We're meeting a woman who
is redefining what it means

21:37.997 --> 21:39.766
to be a transwoman in Brazil.

21:39.799 --> 21:42.068
We're here to interview
Carol Marra,

21:42.101 --> 21:45.104
who is a transwoman who broke
through as a model,

21:45.137 --> 21:47.540
who's now shifting to acting,

21:47.574 --> 21:51.644
did the first trans kiss
on Brazil television, ever.

21:51.678 --> 21:53.045
Ellen. Nice to meet you.

21:53.079 --> 21:54.847
-Ian. Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

21:54.881 --> 21:57.384
PAGE: So, what's going on today?
You're doing a photo shoot?

22:08.428 --> 22:09.962
DANIEL: Thanks so much
for letting us watch you today

22:09.996 --> 22:11.598
at your photo shoot.

22:11.631 --> 22:13.866
You seem really confident
and really, like, into it.

22:24.644 --> 22:27.113
What was your life like growing
up, and where are you from?

22:55.642 --> 22:57.444
Has your family
changed at all?

22:57.477 --> 22:59.011
Like,
are they coming around?

23:41.688 --> 23:44.691
So, then, how do you feel that
you've overcome those odds?

23:55.602 --> 23:58.037
You know, I want to say that
your confidence does spread.

23:58.070 --> 23:59.606
It's very infectious.

23:59.639 --> 24:00.773
And I feel more confident
being around you.

24:00.807 --> 24:02.074
It's like
an infectious thing.

24:04.911 --> 24:06.579
It's a beautiful thing.

24:06.613 --> 24:10.016
You interview people who are
filled with such strength

24:10.049 --> 24:13.252
and beauty and hope and courage.

24:13.285 --> 24:14.887
We're all born
into a homophobic society.

24:14.921 --> 24:16.823
We just are.

24:16.856 --> 24:20.226
We're in some places that are
better than others, no doubt.

24:20.259 --> 24:24.130
But the moment
you are a conscious being,

24:24.163 --> 24:26.799
every story you're told,
every movie you see,

24:26.833 --> 24:29.201
almost every song you hear
is heterosexual,

24:29.235 --> 24:31.203
and typically
also hetero-sexist.

24:31.237 --> 24:34.273
And infused in you
is a feeling of shame.

24:34.306 --> 24:36.609
And sometimes I think
you don't even know

24:36.643 --> 24:39.612
how much that's affecting you
for a really, really long time.

24:39.646 --> 24:41.914
Particularly after coming out,

24:41.948 --> 24:46.052
it became so clear to me
how much that held me back.

24:46.085 --> 24:50.122
I just wish people
could get over it.

24:50.156 --> 24:53.660
There's gay people.
There's trans people.

24:53.693 --> 24:55.928
Can we move on?

25:00.700 --> 25:01.534
PAGE: Here we are
in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil,

25:03.636 --> 25:05.972
which is an absolutely
gorgeous city.

25:06.005 --> 25:08.741
Seems like just
a stunning urban paradise.

25:08.775 --> 25:12.612
And we're here to explore
the LGBT culture

25:12.645 --> 25:14.547
and what people here are facing.

25:14.581 --> 25:17.584
At first glance,

25:17.617 --> 25:19.986
Brazil is a welcoming place
for the gay traveler.

25:20.019 --> 25:24.323
It's been on the forefront of
LGBTQ rights in South America,

25:24.356 --> 25:26.926
being the first country
in the southern hemisphere

25:26.959 --> 25:30.329
to allow gay people to marry
and adopt children.

25:30.362 --> 25:31.998
It's also home

25:32.031 --> 25:34.166
to the largest number
of Catholics in the world,

25:34.200 --> 25:38.905
and in recent years has seen a
rise in conservative evangelism.

25:38.938 --> 25:40.940
These religious conservatives

25:40.973 --> 25:43.876
regard homosexuality
as an abomination,

25:43.910 --> 25:46.345
and some even perform exorcisms

25:46.378 --> 25:50.049
to rid the body
of homosexual tendencies.

25:50.082 --> 25:51.217
[ Groaning ]

25:51.250 --> 25:53.185
And now this religious extremism

25:53.219 --> 25:55.622
is having an influence
on politics,

25:55.655 --> 25:58.024
which is threatening
to repeal progressive laws

25:58.057 --> 26:00.660
and undermine the rights
of the queer community.

26:00.693 --> 26:02.995
[ Speaking Portuguese ]

26:09.969 --> 26:12.805
PAGE: Jair Bolsonaro
is a right-wing congressman

26:12.839 --> 26:15.875
and a major voice in
the anti-gay movement in Brazil.

26:15.908 --> 26:17.810
And he's agreed to meet with me.

26:17.844 --> 26:19.946
So it's gonna be
very interesting

26:19.979 --> 26:22.348
to have an honest discussion
to understand

26:22.381 --> 26:27.253
why he has such difficulty
with accepting LGBT people here.

26:27.286 --> 26:30.289
I definitely feel, like,
a little nervous,

26:30.322 --> 26:34.060
but I'm also interested
to just go meet a human being

26:34.093 --> 26:37.029
and have a discussion
and attempt to understand.

26:37.063 --> 26:40.266
Thank you so much
for meeting with us today.

26:40.299 --> 26:42.268
I know you're a very,
very busy man,

26:42.301 --> 26:45.104
and we really appreciate
your generosity of your time.

26:57.283 --> 26:58.985
Thank you. Well,
thank you for doing that.

26:59.018 --> 27:01.921
I believe you know why we're
here and what we're making.

27:01.954 --> 27:03.055
Maybe you could describe

27:03.089 --> 27:04.857
a little your
political background

27:04.891 --> 27:07.126
and your current role
in government as a deputy.

27:24.811 --> 27:27.346
I've personally read things
you've said,

27:27.379 --> 27:28.848
and the things you've said,

27:28.881 --> 27:30.717
to me, come across
as very homophobic.

27:30.750 --> 27:33.452
And, you know, I mean, you can,
of course, you know,

27:33.485 --> 27:35.788
defend that now
or explain it to me.

27:35.822 --> 27:37.990
But I read a quote
that said

27:38.024 --> 27:41.260
someone should beat the gay
out of their son.

27:41.293 --> 27:44.130
And I'm wondering, I'm gay,
so do you think

27:44.163 --> 27:46.933
that I should have been beaten
as a child,

27:46.966 --> 27:48.801
to not be gay now?

28:32.779 --> 28:34.747
Well, that's the issue
right there,

28:34.781 --> 28:36.415
is you do not think
it's normal.

28:36.448 --> 28:39.318
You say that you should beat
your gay child,

28:39.351 --> 28:41.788
and you've said that you'd
rather your son be dead

28:41.821 --> 28:43.089
than gay.

28:58.237 --> 29:00.439
And you thinking
it's not normal,

29:00.472 --> 29:03.810
it produces all this prejudice
and all this hate.

29:03.843 --> 29:05.778
It turns into shame
in people.

29:05.812 --> 29:07.947
And if they're getting
made fun of,

29:07.980 --> 29:10.817
it turns into severe depression
and suicide.

29:39.311 --> 29:42.114
Well, as a gay person,
if I can make you feel better

29:42.148 --> 29:44.050
about this fear
you seem to have,

29:44.083 --> 29:46.252
I don't want anyone to be gay
who's not gay.

29:46.285 --> 29:48.855
I want gay people who are
suffering and in the closet

29:48.888 --> 29:51.157
and suicidal to be okay
and to love who they are.

29:51.190 --> 29:53.325
But I don't want people
who aren't gay to be gay.

29:53.359 --> 29:56.896
Except maybe Kate Winslet.
[ Laughs ]

29:59.999 --> 30:03.035
All jokes aside,
Bolsonaro is a politician

30:03.069 --> 30:06.038
with a great deal
of power and influence.

30:06.072 --> 30:07.907
And it's devastating to know

30:07.940 --> 30:10.276
that someone
with so much influence

30:10.309 --> 30:13.212
has such a disdain
for the queer community.

30:13.245 --> 30:15.447
We've come to City Hall
to hear firsthand

30:15.481 --> 30:17.149
the stories of families

30:17.183 --> 30:21.187
who have lost loved ones
in violent homophobic attacks.

30:21.220 --> 30:24.056
I'm meeting with Gilmaria
and Marco,

30:24.090 --> 30:26.025
the mother and boyfriend of Tom,

30:26.058 --> 30:28.594
who was tragically killed
a few months ago.

30:28.627 --> 30:30.562
If you feel okay about it,

30:30.596 --> 30:34.133
we'd love if you wanted
to maybe share with us

30:34.166 --> 30:39.138
a little about your case, and
what you've been dealing with.

30:39.171 --> 30:40.472
MARCO: Somebody calls me,

30:40.506 --> 30:42.441
one of his --
one of his friends,

30:42.474 --> 30:45.611
and tells me that
he's in the hospital,

30:45.644 --> 30:48.380
victim of two stabs
in the neck.

30:48.414 --> 30:51.650
And then my world crumbled
right there.

30:51.683 --> 30:53.886
Do you think he was, you know,

30:53.920 --> 30:56.855
targeted specifically
because he was gay?

31:22.281 --> 31:25.217
And so, were the people
who did this,

31:25.251 --> 31:28.520
were they people
that were people you knew,

31:28.554 --> 31:32.925
who were sort of in your world
already, or were they strangers?

32:03.689 --> 32:05.958
He's very beautiful.

32:05.992 --> 32:09.295
[ Sniffles ]

32:09.328 --> 32:11.463
I'm so, so sorry.

32:11.497 --> 32:13.065
Thank you.

32:13.099 --> 32:16.368
Should I wrap it?
Um...

32:16.402 --> 32:19.438
Thank you so much, uh,
for coming

32:19.471 --> 32:22.374
and being so open-hearted
and sharing your story.

32:22.408 --> 32:27.279
Um, I cannot begin
to imagine the pain.

32:36.622 --> 32:38.224
I'm so sorry.

32:44.630 --> 32:46.732
**

32:46.765 --> 32:49.068
PAGE: A large part
of Rio's landscape

32:49.101 --> 32:51.370
is occupied by favelas.

32:51.403 --> 32:53.205
And it's in places like this

32:53.239 --> 32:56.408
where the highest percentage
of LGBTQ murders take place.

32:56.442 --> 33:01.480
**

33:01.513 --> 33:02.681
DANIEL: Wow.

33:02.714 --> 33:05.417
I'm totally kind
of blown away by it.

33:05.451 --> 33:08.154
We're in one of the largest
favelas in Rio.

33:08.187 --> 33:10.489
Over 300,000 people
live in this area,

33:10.522 --> 33:13.025
and you'll see
it's on a high hilltop.

33:13.059 --> 33:17.429
So the government has installed
these hovering cable cars

33:17.463 --> 33:21.033
for people to be able to get
from one area to the next.

33:21.067 --> 33:23.635
So, every year there's
a gay-pride parade

33:23.669 --> 33:25.471
that happens in this favela.

33:25.504 --> 33:29.475
Last year, the organizer
of the parade was shot.

33:29.508 --> 33:33.212
So we're here to kind of explore
what's going on this year,

33:33.245 --> 33:35.447
if there are tensions
in the area,

33:35.481 --> 33:39.551
what it's like to be gay and
to hang out here for Carnival.

33:45.257 --> 33:48.127
What did he say?

33:48.160 --> 33:49.628
Tell me what he's saying.

33:49.661 --> 33:51.263
MAN: He said are you taking
the piss out of him?

33:51.297 --> 33:53.699
No, no, no, not at all.
In fact, the opposite.

33:53.732 --> 33:55.301
You can tell him
that I'm the same way.

34:02.174 --> 34:05.711
Yes, come on, now.
No making fun of anybody.

34:05.744 --> 34:07.579
Making fun of myself.

34:07.613 --> 34:09.648
Come on, now.
[ Laughs ]

34:09.681 --> 34:13.585
What is it like to be gay
and live in a favela in Brazil?

34:29.501 --> 34:31.770
PAGE: As we've seen
throughout Carnival season,

34:31.803 --> 34:34.740
there seems to be a practice
of cross-dressing,

34:34.773 --> 34:36.675
particularly among the men.

34:36.708 --> 34:38.344
But in talking to some of them,

34:38.377 --> 34:40.846
we realized this was more
about a dress-up tradition

34:40.879 --> 34:43.682
rather than a reflection
of tolerance or their identity.

34:43.715 --> 34:47.085
So, you obviously don't normally
dress like this, or do you?

35:13.279 --> 35:14.546
Wow!

35:14.580 --> 35:16.315
[ Laughs ]

35:16.348 --> 35:18.450
[ Drumming ]

35:21.553 --> 35:23.755
I'm kind of dizzy.

35:23.789 --> 35:25.357
How do I look?

35:25.391 --> 35:27.893
PAGE: Today's spirit
of acceptance and abandon

35:27.926 --> 35:29.695
is inspiring.

35:29.728 --> 35:32.798
But these communities
are still vulnerable to danger.

35:35.434 --> 35:38.604
We're nearing the end
of our time in Brazil,

35:38.637 --> 35:40.606
and one final meeting looms.

35:40.639 --> 35:42.708
A meeting which, if I'm honest,

35:42.741 --> 35:44.943
I'm not even sure
I want to have.

35:44.976 --> 35:48.947
**

35:48.980 --> 35:52.751
Right now we're on our way
to go interview a gentleman

35:52.784 --> 35:55.687
who we'll be interviewing
anonymously,

35:55.721 --> 35:57.656
and happens to be a cop.

35:57.689 --> 36:00.759
But he also happens
to be someone

36:00.792 --> 36:06.565
who really hates homosexuals,
and has killed gay people,

36:06.598 --> 36:09.468
um, and also sometimes works
as a contract killer.

36:09.501 --> 36:16.542
We're gonna go talk to him
and try and gain an idea

36:16.575 --> 36:21.380
of why he has such hatred
towards LGBT people.

36:48.039 --> 36:49.608
We know that you're a cop

36:49.641 --> 36:51.977
that you also did other work
on the side.

36:52.010 --> 36:54.846
And we're wondering if,
maybe in your own words,

36:54.880 --> 36:56.782
you could describe
that work.

37:14.866 --> 37:17.936
So when you say that you were
keeping peace on the streets,

37:17.969 --> 37:19.938
what exactly did that work
entail?

37:37.556 --> 37:40.392
And how did you know
that those people were gay?

37:40.426 --> 37:41.860
The way they acted?

37:41.893 --> 37:45.464
Did you kill gay men
and gay women as well?

38:06.552 --> 38:09.955
How many gay people do you
think that you've killed?

38:14.793 --> 38:18.864
Did you not at all feel
like killing gay people

38:18.897 --> 38:20.932
was interfering
with what your job was,

38:20.966 --> 38:23.635
what you were being paid to do,
to protect people?

38:44.423 --> 38:47.893
But -- I'm...

38:47.926 --> 38:50.028
I want to say
that I'm gay.

38:50.061 --> 38:52.097
Do you think
that's safe?

38:52.130 --> 38:53.699
Maybe later.

38:53.732 --> 38:55.901
[ Indistinct conversation ]

39:02.508 --> 39:03.709
Do you want me
to say you, too, or no?

39:03.742 --> 39:06.378
-Yeah.
-Okay.

39:06.412 --> 39:08.614
We're gay,
and I'm wondering

39:08.647 --> 39:12.951
if you think it's better
for the world for us to be dead.

39:26.832 --> 39:29.868
PAGE: I'm standing in front of
a serial killer of gay people,

39:29.901 --> 39:33.138
and I've just revealed
that Ian and I are gay.

39:50.822 --> 39:53.492
What is it exactly about it
that troubles you

39:53.525 --> 39:56.094
to such a degree that
you want to kill people?

40:17.983 --> 40:21.052
How old was he when he --
when he told you he was gay,

40:21.086 --> 40:23.121
and did he just come right out
and tell you about it,

40:23.154 --> 40:24.590
or you found out
another way?

40:39.070 --> 40:40.839
So did he just disappear?

40:40.872 --> 40:43.875
Is he -- did he run away?
Where did he go?

41:02.594 --> 41:05.597
Are there a lot of other men
out there like you?

41:10.001 --> 41:11.537
That are killing
gay people?

41:14.840 --> 41:17.142
This is probably one
of the longest conversations

41:17.175 --> 41:19.711
you've had with two gay people,
or one gay person.

41:19.745 --> 41:21.980
How are you feeling,
talking to us right now?

41:26.585 --> 41:31.757
Well, this is obviously
really hard for us to listen to.

41:31.790 --> 41:33.759
Um...

41:33.792 --> 41:37.162
Yeah, it's -- it's something
that we will never forget.

42:16.267 --> 42:19.738
It does leave you speechless,
honestly.

42:19.771 --> 42:22.173
It's hard, because he looks
like such a fragile, old man

42:22.207 --> 42:24.275
that has some sort of heart
in there that...

42:24.309 --> 42:25.944
You know,
that's what it's like.

42:25.977 --> 42:27.979
Can you get in there a little
bit and crack

42:28.013 --> 42:29.214
a little ounce of love
out of you...

42:29.247 --> 42:30.782
I mean, I don't think so.

42:30.816 --> 42:32.317
...for people that
are different than you?

42:32.350 --> 42:34.119
And it didn't seem
like that was possible.

42:34.152 --> 42:35.821
And on some level,
you feel hopeless,

42:35.854 --> 42:37.889
because it doesn't seem like
there's a way to stop it.

42:37.923 --> 42:39.324
There's no justice
for these people.

42:39.357 --> 42:41.092
It seems like
nothing's even talked about.

42:41.126 --> 42:42.861
No one even knows
who these people are.

42:42.894 --> 42:44.763
You know, because it's like,
"How do you stop that?"

42:57.375 --> 43:00.211
PAGE: I've never stood in front
of someone in my life

43:00.245 --> 43:03.248
who would think it's better
for the world to have me dead.

43:03.281 --> 43:04.950
And there's lots
of those people,

43:04.983 --> 43:06.985
but I've never stood
in front of one of them,

43:07.018 --> 43:09.287
and who's killed many people

43:09.320 --> 43:12.824
of the minority
that you're a part of.

43:12.858 --> 43:15.661
It's a crazy-ass experience.

43:18.764 --> 43:21.166
This trip to Brazil
has been intense.

43:21.199 --> 43:23.669
On the one hand, I experienced

43:23.702 --> 43:27.072
a vibrant, fun,
and proud queer community.

43:27.105 --> 43:31.943
And on the other, a deep-rooted
hatred towards LGBTQ people.

43:31.977 --> 43:35.180
Like so many aspects
of Brazilian life,

43:35.213 --> 43:38.049
the contrasts here are extreme.

43:38.083 --> 43:41.319
But it's impossible
not to be inspired by people

43:41.352 --> 43:42.921
that live so freely,

43:42.954 --> 43:45.824
and in such joyous celebration
of who they are,

43:45.857 --> 43:49.895
especially in the face
of violence and intimidation.

43:49.928 --> 43:52.864
I hope that the spirit
of Carnival,

43:52.898 --> 43:56.201
the spirit of love
and acceptance and joy,

43:56.234 --> 43:58.403
is what wins out in the end.
